      <scopecontent id="aspace_18c326af0179d388f11ccfc83415a7c5">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection contains the personal diaries of John Lewis Gaddis. Subjects include his academic and publishing activities, events in his personal life, his transition to Yale University from Ohio University in the late 1990s, and the founding of the Brady-Johnson Program in Grand Strategy at Yale University. The majority of the diairy entries are typed; some are handwritten.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
